                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Iddings</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee states that Mr. Iddings’s testimony may be given on terms consistent
                    with representative dignity. Unless interrogatory in open court is
                    indispensable, personal deposition at the embassy is preferable.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
